sentences: Kevin Bivona (born November 8, 1986) is an American musician and audio engineer best known for his work with The Transplants and Tim Armstrong.
He is currently the guitarist for the ska punk band The Interrupters.
In 2005, Bivona became the touring keyboard player for The Transplants on the Vans Warped Tour.
On March 2, 2011, Bivona appeared on The Tonight Show with Jay Leno with Travis Barker and Cypress Hill, performing "The Beat Goes On" off Barker's debut solo album.
